last_episode_to_air.name: Never Too Late to Start Again
last_episode_to_air.overview: June and Novak have it out. Theo risks his life for a patient and makes a big decision. Bash rises to the occasion during an emergency and sees how far he's come.

name: Transplant
overview: Dr. Bashir Hamed, a Syrian doctor with battle-tested skills in emergency medicine, makes the difficult decision to flee his country and build a new life in Canada with his younger sister Amira. Bash works to navigate a new environment after earning a coveted residency in the Emergency Department of one of the best hospitals in Toronto, York Memorial.

seasons.name: Season 4
seasons.overview: Season 4 finds Bash on the precipice of finishing his residency at York Memorial and officially re-qualifying as a doctor. With his future uncertain once again, Bash and his sister Amira are Canadian citizens now, but are still trying, with everything they have, to build a life in their adopted country.

episodes.name: Pilot
episodes.overview: When Bashir Hamed finds himself at the site of a tragic accident, his medical training takes over as he works to save the wounded. At York Memorial Hospital, the staff treat patients from the accident while concerns arise about their Chief of Emergency Medicine, Dr. Jed Bishop.

episodes.name: Tell Me Who You Are
episodes.overview: When Bash and Mags work together to treat a patient with a tricky diagnosis, Mags realizes that Bash’s experience as a doctor in Syria has led to an instinct-based approach. Head nurse Claire Malone is concerned that Dr. Bishop is already working following his accident. June struggles to put her foot down with Dr. Singh concerning the needs of a patient, and Theo works to build a connection with Bash.

episodes.name: Your Secrets Can Kill You
episodes.overview: As Bash's future at the hospital hangs in the balance, he diagnoses a young patient with a rare disease that could have been prevented. Mags is faced with a case she cannot solve, as June tries to keep her personal life private.  Meanwhile, Theo drives through the night to spend a day with his family in Sudbury.

episodes.name: Saleh
episodes.overview: Bash is divided between his work at the hospital and a patient he is helping to treat remotely in Syria. Dr. Bishop puts extra pressure on Bash, while Theo feels powerless when something happens to one of his daughters back home. Meanwhile, a patient puts Mags’ moral convictions to the test, and June tries to improve her social skills.

episodes.name: Eid
episodes.overview: Bash does his best to celebrate Eid with his sister Amira, but she wishes they could continue the traditions they had back home. At the hospital, Bash has difficulty respecting a patient’s decision, while Mags tries to gather all the information they need to save a gunshot victim. Theo treats a teenage patient who wants to avoid telling his parents why he’s in the hospital.

episodes.name: Trigger Warning
episodes.overview: An incident at work causes Bash to second-guess himself. Mags is inspired by a firefighter devoted to her work, even if it means risking her life on a daily basis, and June must learn to work with others. Meanwhile, Theo celebrates his birthday for the first time away from his family, and is faced with a young patient with a big plea.

episodes.name: Far From Home
episodes.overview: Bash wants to make things right with Amira after their lives are turned upside down once again.

episodes.name: Birth and Rebirth
episodes.overview: Bash and Amira settle into a new environment, while at the hospital Bash helps a worried couple expecting their first child. Dr. Bishop puts Mags to the test by personally evaluating her performance in the emergency department. Meanwhile, Theo is surprised by his reaction in the face of an altercation, and Attending Dr. Wendy Atwater gives June an interesting case.

episodes.name: Under Pressure
episodes.overview: Bash provides medical care to a friend who is reluctant about treatment, while Mags has her hands full with a young woman who seems to be withholding information. Dr. Bishop offers Mags an incredible opportunity, and someone from June’s past tries to reach out to her. Faced with a young athlete without a clear diagnosis, Theo also has to navigate the patient’s complicated family dynamic.

episodes.name: Collapse
episodes.overview: When an explosion takes place near the hospital, Bash runs toward the danger. Mags treats a patient without all the information she needs, and June struggles to take initiative. When a schoolgirl is brought into the hospital in cardiac arrest, Theo does everything he can to save her. Through all the chaos, Claire takes the time to help a teenage girl in need.

episodes.name: Orphans
episodes.overview: Bash finds himself connecting with an unlikely patient, while Mags strives to find balance in her life. Theo has a difficult discussion with his wife, Melissa. June attempts to connect with a closed-off teenage patient and Claire take care of a couple checking things off their bucket list.

episodes.name: Relapse
episodes.overview: When a young mother addicted to opioids nearly dies, Bash must figure out whether she's using again, or if something else is causing her deadly symptoms. Mags tries to help a patient who isn't healing properly, while June is blindsided by her father.

episodes.name: The Only Way Out Is Through
episodes.overview: Bash and Mags race to save a woman with mysterious symptoms who was nearly killed by their team's medical error. Theo tries to help a gravely ill teen and his family deal with the possibility that medical hope has run out.

episodes.name: Guardrail
episodes.overview: A bus full of kids crashes and sends the team racing. Bash’s life is upended when he is reunited with a woman from his past. With Dr. Bishop still unconscious after his stroke, Mags struggles to find support in her mentor’s absence. Theo faces repercussions from his family after taking a full-time job away from home, and June has an important career decision to make.

episodes.name: Jasmine
episodes.overview: Rania's arrival triggers unwanted memories for Bash; Mags can't win her new boss' approval.

episodes.name: Sever
episodes.overview: A morbidity and mortality review forces Bash and Dr. Bishop into conflict.

episodes.name: Contact
episodes.overview: As Dr. Bishop faces challenges returning to work, Bash's loyalty is tested; Mags has a harrowing encounter with an aggressive patient.

episodes.name: Roads
episodes.overview: Bash helps his undocumented friend Khaled apply for asylum.

episodes.name: Liberty
episodes.overview: Bash faces an ethical dilemma with a gang member and the police officer looking for him.

episodes.name: Control
episodes.overview: Pressured by a patient's father, Bash must make an impossible choice to save a life.

episodes.name: Scars
episodes.overview: With his future as a doctor on the line, Bash must suppress his instincts and avoid any chance of risk.

episodes.name: Between
episodes.overview: Bash’s focus is split between the needs of patients in two countries; Dr. Bishop’s emergency department goals are met with mixed support.

episodes.name: Shadows
episodes.overview: Bash draws on his war zone experience when harsh weather causes the hospital to lose power.

episodes.name: Locked
episodes.overview: As shakeups force major turmoil at the hospital, Bash and Amira take a trip.

episodes.name: Saviours
episodes.overview: Bash saves a hostile man during his commute and gets some shocking news about his future.

episodes.name: Free for What
episodes.overview: As Bash fights for Dr. Bishop's legacy, big questions about his own future are finally answered.

episodes.name: Fracture
episodes.overview: Bash's decisions lead to conflict with the new chief of emergency medicine; Mags struggles to save a patient who thinks the system gave up on her; June has trouble with her new roommate, and gets a work proposal from Novak; Theo has trouble adapting.

episodes.name: Baggage
episodes.overview: Bash treats a man with a rare medical condition. Mags gets a visit from her parents and goes above and beyond for a pregnant woman with an undiagnosed condition. A misunderstanding with a rabies patient lands Theo in trouble. June and Novak negotiate a tentative working relationship. Devi starts to make changes.

episodes.name: Hospital Beige
episodes.overview: Bash treats a woman whose ketamine therapy goes awry; Mags loses confidence in her new boss; June realizes she has too much on her plate; Theo reunites with a young former patient whose life may depend on the death of another patient.

episodes.name: Multiple Choices
episodes.overview: Bash finds himself at odds with his direct supervisor while they treat a couple of skydivers with a unique relationship; Mags speaks out against her supervising doctor; a mistake comes back to bite Theo.

episodes.name: Nadir
episodes.overview: Recovering from a personal crisis, Mags worries about how to get her life back on track; Bash takes an unorthodox approach to treating a soldier with PTSD; Theo treats a terminally ill child whose father is desperate for a drug trial.

episodes.name: Audition
episodes.overview: Bash and Amira have an argument over her future; Bash treats a diabetic woman who is overly dependent on her 18-year-old son; Mags questions herself as she adjusts to very limited parameters.

episodes.name: Work to Rule
episodes.overview: Bash reels from Amira's bold decision; tensions flare at an after-work dinner party; Devi struggles to keep her staff in line as turmoil erupts over her leadership; Mags treats a highly sensitive person; Theo considers breaking some hospital rules.

episodes.name: And So It Goes
episodes.overview: Bash's life is scrutinized during his citizenship interview; when treating survivors of a building fire, Theo needs Bash's help with a scared young boy; Mags helps a recovering addict who swallowed her keys; June and Bash treat estranged brothers.

episodes.name: Rumination
episodes.overview: Bash's psychiatrist suggests an unexpected form of therapy. Mags gets evicted and meets an old patient who holds a grudge. Theo makes some questionable choices with a patient's mother. June's personal and professional worlds collide.

episodes.name: Unstuck in Time
episodes.overview: Bash tries saving a couple whose wedding was waylaid by gunfire; Mags' demanding teen patient needs birth control; June struggles with an old habit; an activist patient puts Theo in his place.

episodes.name: A Sort of Homecoming
episodes.overview: A software glitch takes down the emergency department; Bash explores new terrain; Mags searches for a new cardiologist; June is fed up with her bosses; Theo attempts a stable dating life.

episodes.name: Tariq
episodes.overview: Bash faces an important figure from his past and must solve a public health crisis; hospital administration calls Devi's leadership into question; Mags doubts all of her choices; June is asked to oversee a sensitive procedure.

episodes.name: The Luxury of Memory
episodes.overview: Bash has a major realization; Mags faces an overwhelming health crisis; Devi stands behind her choices; June confronts loss; Theo witnesses a devastating event.

episodes.name: Crete
episodes.overview: Bash and Mags team up to save a John and Jane Doe found in the woods. A fully qualified surgeon now, June sees her old mentor in a new light. Suspended from the hospital, Theo longs for the action while treating patients virtually. Devi makes a budget cut decision, which will have major consequences for the Emergency Department.

episodes.name: Sinkhole
episodes.overview: Bash jumps into a sinkhole to save a trapped pedestrian. Mags faces a difficult personal choice, while attempting to contain a potential outbreak in the Emergency Department. Theo does whatever it takes to help a boxer with severe chest pain. June connects with a volatile patient, overstepping Novak. Claire is having trouble adjusting after a past assault.

episodes.name: Home
episodes.overview: Bash and Mags fall into friendly competition at work, and a man with superhero ideation crash lands into the Emergency Department. June tries group therapy, and Theo faces a tribunal to decide his fate.

episodes.name: Decisions
episodes.overview: Devi decides between Bash and Mags. Bash helps a young single father with nowhere else to turn. June and Novak take different approaches with a resident. Theo treats a teen patient with a connection close to home. Mags gets life altering news.

episodes.name: Heart
episodes.overview: Mags shares big personal news with her colleagues, which has an effect on Bash. June sees a patient with a specific phobia. Theo bumps against a protective family doctor while trying to help a returning young patient. Claire looks for help but finds Devi stretched thin.

episodes.name: Fever Dream
episodes.overview: Mags undergoes transplant surgery and copes with the aftermath aided by her family and Bash. Bash balances personal and professional stress. June confronts Novak's self-sabotaging behaviour. Theo navigates a visit from his father and thwarts Liz's attempt to meet his family.

episodes.name: Torn
episodes.overview: Bash passes on an opportunity, and works cases where things are not as they appear. Mags returns to York Memorial. June navigates loss professionally and personally. Theo goes out on a limb again for a patient. Claire is confronted by Devi and her colleagues about recent challenges.

episodes.name: All I Have Is How I Feel
episodes.overview: Bash and Mags support each other through new challenges while treating an older couple who show up at the hospital glued together. Theo is called out by Liz Bergeron about his repeated inability to follow hospital rules.

episodes.name: Who Is Mags?
episodes.overview: Bash treats a man injured in a car accident who was saved by the woman who hit him. Devi decides to fight to hold on to the department. In a moment where it is most needed, a former member of the York Memorial team returns.

episodes.name: Never Too Late to Start Again
episodes.overview: June and Novak have it out. Theo risks his life for a patient and makes a big decision. Bash rises to the occasion during an emergency and sees how far he's come.

4.name: Season 4
4.overview: Season 4 finds Bash on the precipice of finishing his residency at York Memorial and officially re-qualifying as a doctor. With his future uncertain once again, Bash and his sister Amira are Canadian citizens now, but are still trying, with everything they have, to build a life in their adopted country.
